Example flights data

flights_data.Rd

A data set of 33 flights processed through the rnp_flights_data function Each row in the data represents the surface temperature measured recorded in a given tile (i.e., unique latitude and longitude combination) at the moment in time when a flight took place (specified by a unique year, day of the year and minute of the day).

Usage

flights_data

Format

A tibble with 263008 rows and 7 columns, all numeric:

longitude

Longitude of a given tile in decimal degrees

latitude

Latitude of a given tile in decimal degrees

ir_temp

Surface temperature measured via an IR camera

year

Year when the flight took place

doy

Day of the year when the flight took place

mod_start

Minute of the day when the flight started

mod_end

Minute of the day when the flight ended

Examples

flights_data
